        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/f0a364/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-01-28T06:26:39.617Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The last Signal blog post mentioned that attachments are padded to improve privacy. How exactly is this padding done? Is the file size rounded up to a certain multiple or is the file split into fixed size chunks? What are the exact values? Thank you very much!</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://signal.org/blog/a-synchronized-start-for-linked-devices/\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/a/0/a070fdcafbe5753b5b412f3e5b5c640cff8d0c48.svg\" class=\"site-icon\" data-dominant-color=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://signal.org/blog/a-synchronized-start-for-linked-devices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Signal Messenger</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/361;\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/0/d/0df92fcd0e8e826f8db0a1ac3ae5786544cabbf9_2_690x362.png\" class=\"thumbnail\" data-dominant-color=\"9EA8A9\" width=\"690\" height=\"362\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://signal.org/blog/a-synchronized-start-for-linked-devices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">A Synchronized Start for Linked Devices</a></h3>\n\n  <p>With Signal on Desktop and iPad, you can link your primary Android or iOS account with another device, letting you check and respond to messages in both places or conduct video meetings and calls from the comfort of a bigger screen. Signal’s upcoming...</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
